  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am having the same issue. In my situation, The parent component used `connectStateResults` and I was passing the `searching` property to the child component which was wrapped with `connectInfiniteHits` causing an infinite loop.\r\n\r\nMy solution was to add a non-connected wrapper around the child component and use that as a direct child of the parent component.\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst Child = connectInfiniteHits((props) => (\r\n    // Hits logic\r\n))\r\n\r\nconst ChildNoConnector = (props) => <Child {...props} />\r\n\r\nconst Parent = connectStateResults(({ searching }) => (\r\n    <ChildNoConnector loading={searching} />\r\n));\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2021-09-03T13:32:45Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5269#issuecomment-1363064284",
